Performance Rules for SmartReno:

Backend / Data:

- Avoid unnecessary database queries
- Never fetch entire tables when a scoped query is sufficient
- Use pagination for lists where appropriate
- Select only the columns actually needed
- Reuse existing indexes and query patterns before proposing new ones
- Keep server-side logic efficient and predictable

Frontend:

- Minimize unnecessary re-renders
- Avoid heavy client-side state when server-driven patterns are better
- Lazy load heavy UI when appropriate
- Keep expensive computations memoized only when actually needed
- Do not over-engineer optimization prematurely

General:

- Favor simple, maintainable performance wins
- Do not sacrifice correctness or security for speed
- Measure before proposing major architectural performance changes

